<Link id="l00880" /><CodeLine lineNumber="880"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// To handle the case like the following:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00881" /><CodeLine lineNumber="881"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    struct t;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00882" /><CodeLine lineNumber="882"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    typedef struct t &#95;t;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00883" /><CodeLine lineNumber="883"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    struct s1 &#123; &#95;t &#42;c; &#125;;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00884" /><CodeLine lineNumber="884"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    int test1(struct s1 &#42;arg) &#123; ... &#125;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00885" /><CodeLine lineNumber="885"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00886" /><CodeLine lineNumber="886"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    struct t &#123; int a; int b; &#125;;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00887" /><CodeLine lineNumber="887"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    struct s2 &#123; &#95;t c; &#125;</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00893" /><CodeLine lineNumber="893"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00897" /><CodeLine lineNumber="897"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// definition won&#39;t be correct.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00898" /><CodeLine lineNumber="898"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00899" /><CodeLine lineNumber="899"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// In the above, we have following debuginfo:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00900" /><CodeLine lineNumber="900"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//  &#123;ptr, struct&#95;member&#125; -&gt;  typedef -&gt; struct</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00903" /><CodeLine lineNumber="903"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//  &#123;different types&#125; -&gt; &#91;various derived types&#93;+ -&gt; another type.</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00905" /><CodeLine lineNumber="905"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//  &#123;func&#95;param, struct&#95;member&#125; -&gt; const -&gt; ptr -&gt; volatile -&gt; struct</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00906" /><CodeLine lineNumber="906"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// We will traverse const/ptr/volatile which already have corresponding</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00909" /><CodeLine lineNumber="909"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (Ty &amp;&amp; (!CheckPointer || !SeenPointer)) &#123;</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00911" /><CodeLine lineNumber="911"><span class="doxyHighlight">        </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">while</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (DTy) &#123;</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00913" /><CodeLine lineNumber="913"><span class="doxyHighlight">          </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (!BaseTy)</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00915" /><CodeLine lineNumber="915"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00916" /><CodeLine lineNumber="916"><span class="doxyHighlight">          </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (DIToIdMap.find(BaseTy) != DIToIdMap.end()) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
